description:
hungry + healing in Thailand  here's a little glimpse into my eat, pray, love journey (except replace 'pray' with eat and 'love' with more eating hehe) If youre struggling, consider therapy with our sponsor BetterHelp. Click https://BetterHelp.com/sun for a 10% discount on your first month of therapy with alicensed professional specific to your needs.

I am in such a better place now with my mental health (the best it's ever been actually ) This video took me a while to bring myself to edit. I started off wanting to document it all and then decided to stop. To REALLY disconnect. *I went to Bangkok, Chiang Mai, Phuket, Krabi and Ko Tao before flying to Bali. But this is what I managed to capture during my first week. And a couple things I learned. And how i started to heal. 

My book of the week: The Midnight Library by Matt Haig

MY ITINERARY: 

BANGKOK: 
Soup noodles: Nai Ek Roll Noodle (442  9, Samphanthawong, Bangkok 10100, Thailand) 

Dessert soup: Nam Dao Huu  (33 Plaeng Nam Rd, Samphanthawong, Bangkok 10100, Thailand)

Pad Thai Fai Ta Lu  (115/5 Dinso Rd, Baworniwet, Phranakorn, Bangkok 10200, Thailand) 10 - 5pm

Kor Panits Sticky Rice- 431 433 Thanon Tanao, San Chao Pho Sua, Phra Nakhon, Bangkok 10200, Thailand

Noodles w. Minced pork: Guay Tiew Mu Rung Rueang Tung (10/3 Soi Sukhumvit 26, Khlong Tan, Bangkok, 10110, Thailand) 

Musical chairs curry: Khao Gaeng Jek Pui (Je Chie) (25 Mangkon Rd, Pom Prap, Pom Prap Sattru Phai, Bangkok 10100) 

Fried noodles: Ann Guay Tiew Kua Gai (419 Luang Rd, Wat Thepsirin, Pom Prap Sattru Phai, Bangkok 10100, Thailand) 

Yaowarat/ Chinatown (i got  PA TONG GO but there are so many yummy things to eat) 

I went on day tour for the Mae Klong Railway Market  (life-risking Market) + Damnoen Saduak (floating market) https://www.getyourguide.com/bangkok-l169/bangkok-damnoen-saduak-market-and-maeklong-railway-market-t383872/

CHIANG MAI: 
Khao Soi Khun Yai (QXWM+47J, Sri Poom 8 Alley, Tambon Si Phum, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand) 

Chiang mai food tour: A Chef's Tour

Chiang mai Cooking class: Thai Akha Kitchen 

Kat's Kitchen: 17 Ratchamanka Rd, Tambon Phra Sing, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Thailand

Chiang Mai Night Bazaar

Chiang Mai's Sunday Market (on Ratchadamnoen Road from 4pm to 10pm)
